modules.description: This module provides operations for parsing and transforming Markdown elements, including handling headings, lists, quotes, and preformatted text through recursive descent parsing and buffer management. It works with structured representations like paragraph lists, token streams, and mutable parsing state, alongside utilities for string manipulation and indentation detection. Typical use cases involve converting Markdown documents into structured ASTs for rendering to HTML or analyzing document structure programmatically.

This module converts Markdown documents into HTML elements using customizable renderers for links, images, and preformatted blocks. It operates on Markdown data types like `paragraph`, `par_text`, and `text`, producing structured HTML elements such as paragraphs, lists, and headings. Concrete use cases include rendering documentation, blog posts, or user-generated content into HTML for web display.
